Web: URL: http://www.cam.sri.com/tr/crc061/paper.ps.ZProceedings  
Date: 1996  
Abstract: We describe how substantial domain-independent language-processing systems for French and Spanish were quickly developed by manually adapting an existing English-language system, the SRI Core Language Engine. We explain the adaptation process in detail, and argue that it provides a fairly general recipe for converting a grammar-based system for English into a corresponding one for a Romance lan guage.
